cs.DL, cs.SI, cs.IR, cs.CY, cs.SD 

The paper investigates gender differences in citation and readership impact of academic publications, which is relevant to several sub-categories in computer science. cs.DL (Digital Libraries) is the most likely category as it deals with the analysis and management of scholarly publications. cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) and cs.IR (Information Retrieval) are also likely as they deal with the dissemination and impact of information. cs.CY (Computers and Society) and cs.SD (Software Engineering) are less likely but still relevant as they deal with social and ethical issues in computer science and the impact of software on society.
